Responsibilities:

Analyze the market trend and keep the clients updated with market information
Work closely with relationship managers to maintain and facilitate the sales of investment products
Provide professional recommendations of investment products;
Monitor customers’ investment portfolios and provide advices to achieve target returns;
Alert client for any significant market movement and make suggestions on time;
Facilitate trade dealing and prepare relevant documents;
Ensure proper conduct and selling procedures are complied with rules and regulations

Ideal candidates should possess:

Bachelor’s degree or above in Business Studies, major in Finance or related discipline preferred;
At least 8 years’ relevant work experience serving the high net-worth clients;
Experience in dealing investment products, including equity, fixed income products, mutual funds and structured products;
Experience in alternative investment, i.e. Private Equity Fund, will be highly appreciated;
Knowledge of Banking Ordinance, Securities and Futures Ordinance and related Codes is preferred;
Relevant Individual with SFC Type 1 license is a must;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Self-motivated with strong customer service mindset;
Proficient in written and spoken English and Chinese (Mandarin & Cantonese)

We offer attractive remuneration package and comprehensive fringe benefits. Interested parties please e-mail your full resume with current and expected salary by clicking "Apply Now". 

Personal information collected will be used for considering suitability for the post and strictly in accordance with our personal data policies.  It is our policy to retain the personal data of unsuccessful applicants for future recruitment purposes for a period of maximum two years.

Our client is a European Private Banking to cope with the rapid business expansion, they are now inviting high caliber candidates to join the team

Associate ,Financial Crime Compliance ( Private Banking) - Compliance Department 

Responsibilities:

Assist the Head of Financial Crime to establish, review and update the AML related guidelines, policies and procedural manuals to ensure they are in line with Group and regulatory requirements;
Review and investigate transactions triggered by monitoring systems or escalated by front office or other monitoring parties for potential financial crime risks; Report suspicious transactions and escalate for management oversight timely to ensure adequate follow up actions and ongoing monitoring;
Monitor effective operation of AML tools and processes for transaction monitoring, client screening, payment screening and client risk assessment; Escalate issues for timely resolution and manage necessary remediation;
Conduct regular recalibration and tuning of parameters and drive enhancements for AML tools and systems;
Review escalated alerts stopped on payment screening system and escalate transactions potentially related to money laundering and sanctions;
Review alerts from ongoing client screening and manage the escalation of true hits for risk reclassification and monitoring follow up actions;
Trigger follow up actions and KYC updates upon irregularities noted from transaction monitoring or client screening;
Assist the Head of AML / Compliance in preparing internal AML training materials;
Prepare materials for periodic AML governance meetings;
Perform ad hoc tasks as assigned by Head of AML/Compliance from time to time;
Assist in audits and inspections, and investigations where required
Involvement in special work projects as and when required
Assist Head of Compliance, Hong Kong and the Compliance team in any other work matters;
Must solid exp in transaction monitoring and manage AML tools and System 

Competencies:

Basic bachelor degree;  
5 – 8 years of relevant experience in general compliance and financial crime compliance in private banking industry 
Must solid exp in transaction monitoring and manage AML tools and System 
A keen interest to learn and perform compliance matters;
Good interactive, communication and writing skills;
Able to provide alternative solutions to business;
Motivated and innovative; able to handle issues and resolve challenges in collaboration with colleagues;
Team player

Please send full resume with present & expected salary to expedite sourcing in MS-WORD format by clicking “APPLY NOW”
Please quote our reference in your application
Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with the employer’s personal data policies, a copy of which will be provided upon request
All information provided will be used for recruitment purpose only

Job Responsibilities:

Provide banking services toward UHNW/HNW private wealth management customers
Provide marketing and training support to group staff;
Provide customers with one-stop financial services, such as financial asset allocation recommendations, lead investment banking services, family office service, offshore trust needs understanding and planning services.
Deepen and establish long-term customer relationships by determining customer needs for financial services, including but not limited to providing investment, insurance and other banking products and services;
Plan and provide relevant and appropriate financial products and services to meet the needs of existing and potential customers;
Cooperate with relevant departments and personnel inside and outside the group to initiate and implement the marketing strategy/plan of wealth management products/services;
Achieve key performance indicators;
Support cross-border business activities in the PWM field;
Strictly comply with compliance requirements, ensure that product information is prepared for internal parties and comply with regulatory requirements and rules;
Assist in system development and improvement projects of financial products/services;
If necessary, instruct and train junior staff;
Coordinate marketing and promotional activities inside and outside the branch when necessary.

Job Requirements:

Hold a university degree or above in business, major in finance or business related; pass HKSI Paper 1, 7 and 8 and IIQE Paper 1 and 3;
At least 3 years of experience related to private banking/asset management sales, distribution sales experience will be an advantage;
Have cross-border business experience, willingness and compliance awareness;
Possess good teamwork spirit, interpersonal communication skills and understanding; able to be independent and able to complete work under pressure;
Possess good analytical skills, and can have a comprehensive understanding of various wealth management products (including but not limited to stocks, public funds, private funds, fixed income products, structured products and insurance), as well as roadshows and training capabilities;
Have the ability to establish, operate and maintain pipeline relationships with internal partners;
Fluent Chinese (Mandarin) English listening, speaking, reading and writing skills;
Proficient in MS Word, Excel and PowerPoint;
CFA, CFP, FRM and other professional qualifications are preferred;

Basel Capital is a multi-family office based in Hong Kong specialized in private real estate investments. We partner with ultra-high net worth families and provide holistic wealth management and investment advisory services.
This position is based in Central, Hong Kong and open due to the expansion of our group.
For more information, please refer to our website basecg.com and baselpe.com.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for a portfolio of Private Banking (EAM) and their wealthy clients to provide sophisticated advice on solutions;
Promote full range of Private Banking (EAM) and family office services and achieve the Company’s objectives as well as revenue targets;
Develop and maintain long-term client network through effective relationship management, with extensive focus on the clients' financial analysis, protection and investment objectives;
Ensure the grow of the client base to significantly contribute to the aggregation of AUM;
Daily telephone contact and meetings with sophisticated clients as well as negotiations with internal interfaces;
Deliver top service to clients and ensure smooth administration;
Initiate account openings / closures / update instruction checklists and interface with client to ensure completion of documentation requirements;
Maintain a close working relationship with the EAM team and private banks to ensure the continued viability of client objectives and management of client assets
Effectively coordinate with the Company’s teams and strategic partners to develop appropriate strategies and solutions;
Handle financial transactions and product enquiries as well as all categories of customer service matters;
Provide guidance, coaching and support to junior members.

 Requirements:

A university degree, ideally in Banking, Finance, Business Administration or Economics.
Minimum 5 years of experience as a Relationship Manager, Business Development or Investment Advisor in the EAM, Private Banking, HNWI or Asset Management business;
Sound knowledge of various types of private banking products;
Qualified to carry out Investment regulated activities (Types 4 and 9) under Securities and Futures Ordinance (SFO) is a must;
Strong client skills combined with the ability to communicate efficiently at all levels are some of your strengths;
A standout colleague with excellent organizational skills and a structured and efficient approach;
Able to contribute and deliver high-end dedicated service in a dynamic work environment;
Proficiency in spoken and written English and Chinese, excellent in Putonghua is preferred.

Please send your full resume with current and expected salary and availability by clicking “Apply Now”.
All information collected will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. (Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)

