Basel Capital is a multi-family office based in Hong Kong specialized in private real estate investments. We partner with ultra-high net worth families and provide holistic wealth management and investment advisory services.
This position is based in Central, Hong Kong and open due to the expansion of our group.
For more information, please refer to our website basecg.com and baselpe.com.

Responsibilities:

Provide general public markets investment and portfolio management support to senior management
Collect market information and identify investment opportunities on the financial market;
Assist in portfolio management and investment research in U.S. real estate and property markets
Develop detailed financial models and prepare investment research reports;
Conduct research, due diligence, financial and industry analysis, investment memorandum preparation, and investment execution for private equity investments;
Prepare meeting materials for internal meetings such as annual reviews, return projections and others;
Perform regular and ad-hoc assigned responsibilities and duties that are related to managerial and operational requirements.

 Requirements:

At least 2-3 years of experience in asset management, private equity or investment banking;
Bachelor degree holder in Finance, Economics, Accounting, Business, or related discipline
Qualified to carry out Investment regulated activities (Types 4 and 9) under Securities and Futures Ordinance (SFO) preferred;
Strong analytical and presentation skills;
Solid knowledge of financial modelling and project management;
Hands-on experience in research, presentation preparation and data mining;
Able to work independently and under pressure;
Proficient in both written and spoken English, Mandarin and Cantonese.

Please send your full resume with current and expected salary and availability by clicking “Apply Now”.
All information collected will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. (Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)

Credit Risk Manager / Vice President (Private Bank)

Responsibilities:

Review and approve Lombard lending proposals within delegated authority to ensure that the bank’s credit offering is in compliance with bank’s policies, procedures, risk appetite and local regulatory requirements;
Provide recommendations and highlight key risk issues to front office and credit approvers;
Review and approve Credit Exception requests and Loan-to-Value ratio for Lombard Lending requests. Evaluate credit risk based on overall analysis of counterparty, collateral’s risk dynamics, client’s portfolio holdings;
Provide training and guidance to Relationship Managers / Client Services Officers on credit policies and processes (including preparation of credit proposals);
Assist the department head in managing the loan portfolio and collateral of designated business unit;
Prepare periodic credit risk portfolio report and risk management committee meeting minutes;
Participate in credit policy / new product programme review and ad-hoc projects;
Coach junior Credit Officers, Relationship Managers and Client Services Officers on credit assessment competency.

Requirements:

Degree holder in Finance, Business and related disciplines. Holder of The Enhanced Competency Framework on Credit Risk Management (ECF-CRM) is a plus;
At least 8-12 years of relevant experience in Private Banking;
Good understanding of business strategy, plans and objectives of financial institutions. Ability to provide appropriate support in development and implementation of such strategies and objectives by identifying and mitigating external threats and risks;
Strong technical knowledge of credit approval process, systems and controls and credit risk management of financial institutions;
Strong financial and credit analysis, collateral management (credit monitoring and control) skills;
Strong knowledge of wealth management and private banking products (bonds, equities, structured notes, funds, etc.);
Sound working knowledge of Hong Kong Company & Banking Law, Credit Policies and Collateral Management policies;
Excellent ability to communicate with stakeholders of all levels;
Excellent initiative with ability to work independently;
Proficiency in English, Cantonese and Mandarin.

Attractive remuneration and fringe benefits will be offered to the successful candidate.

Interested candidates should apply with detailed resume, present and expected salaries by clicking the Apply Now button.

All information received will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.

Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.
